data.title: Sarah Kennedy, granddaughter of Robert F. Kennedy, marries at family compound
data.meta_description: Sarah Kennedy, the granddaughter of assassinated politician Robert F Kennedy and wife Ethel, has tied the k...
data.text:
Sarah Kennedy, the granddaughter of assassinated politician Robert F. Kennedy and wife Ethel, has tied the knot at the family compound in Hyannis Port in Massachusetts in the US.

Sarah wed Jam Sulahry at the Kennedy compound, surrounded by family and friends.

Little is know about the couple however it is known that Sarah is working as a partner at Hanold Associates HR & Diversity Executive Search and Advisory and Sulahry continues his studies at Harvard Business School.

READ MORE: 'None of us wanted': Royals break silence over loss

Sarah's parents are Christopher and Sheila Kennedy and the niece of Robert F. Kennedy Jr who is currently vying to be the Republican candidate for the US presidential election in 2024.

Sarah told PEOPLE, who covered the event exclusively, they chose the Kennedy compound for their wedding "because of how special it is to us as a backdrop to our lives."

"It is where we have celebrated the great times and come together in heartbreaking times," she continued.

"It truly feels like coming home."

While the reception took place this weekend, their legal wedding took place on June 17, 2022, in a small Pakistani ceremony called a Nikah, in keeping with the groom's family's tradition.

The most romantic royal wedding kisses of all time

The date coincided with the 72nd anniversary of Robert and Ethel Kennedy's own wedding.

Sarah shared the story of how she met her husband, explaining they both attended Boston College and met the night before classes began.

That night the students visited their local Target store to pick up last-minute items they need for their dorms.

"In Aisle 10, Jam laid eyes on [me] for the first time and asked, 'Want to shop with me?'" she shared.

They soon began dating, with their love story progressing to this special nuptials.

"Getting married is about memorializing our love for each other and our commitment to each other for life," Sarah told PEOPLE. "We were best friends before dating and grew our relationship through good times and bad. Marriage is the next chapter in our love story, and we couldn't be happier."

The pair shared that they will honeymoon in Greece and Italy before returning home.
